# Companion source files installed into vendored tokio after the .patch applies.
# Format: <src (relative to this patch dir)> <dest (relative to vendor/tokio-*)>
# The 0001-tokio-wasi-process.patch wires `#[path = "wasi.rs"] mod imp;` for
# target_os = "wasi"; this installs that module (the cooperative single-thread
# process impl: Child::poll does WNOHANG try_wait + yield, never blocking the
# executor). Without it the patched tokio fails to compile (missing wasi.rs).
wasi-process-imp.rs src/process/wasi.rs
